WEBVTT

00:05.539 --> 00:06.073 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Good evening. I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.106 --> 00:07.708 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
On the NEWSHOUR tonight:

00:07.741 --> 00:13.146 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A vow to defeat ISIS. President Obama looks
ahead to his final year in office, in his

00:13.180 --> 00:16.550 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
end of 2015 news conference.

00:16.583 --> 00:21.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's Friday. Mark Shields and David Brooks
are here to analyze what the president said

00:21.521 --> 00:23.724 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and the rest of the week's news.

00:23.757 --> 00:29.863 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, we head to the set of "Downton Abbey"
for a look at how the British drama has captivated

00:29.897 --> 00:30.697 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
American audiences.

00:30.731 --> 00:32.432 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

00:32.466 --> 00:36.303 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ELIZABETH MCGOVERN, ACTRESS: The one extraordinary
difference is that, every word is written

00:36.336 --> 00:43.477 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by one man. I don't know of any other television
show that works that way. And I, to this day,

00:43.510 --> 00:44.745 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
find it absolutely mindboggling.

00:44.778 --> 00:45.879 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

00:45.913 --> 00:54.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: All that and more on tonight's PBS
NEWSHOUR.

00:54.688 --> 00:58.191 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:58.225 --> 01:07.134 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: From President Obama today, a year-end
promise to target terror in the year to come.

01:07.167 --> 01:12.239 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He spoke at a White House news conference,
and sought again to allay public fears of

01:12.272 --> 01:18.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
potential attacks. At home, he called for
Americans to stay vigilant, and overseas,

01:18.045 --> 01:21.014 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he promised to pound away at the Islamic State
group.

01:21.048 --> 01:22.716 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

01:22.749 --> 01:24.484 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES:
ISIL's already lost about 40 percent of the

01:24.518 --> 01:30.624 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
populated areas it once controlled in Iraq,
and it's losing territory in Syria. Now, squeezing

01:30.657 --> 01:36.263 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIL's heart, its core in Syria and Iraq,
will make it harder for them to pump their

01:36.296 --> 01:38.532 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
terror and propaganda to the rest of the world.

01:38.565 --> 01:40.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

01:40.167 --> 01:42.703 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: We'll have an extended report on
the president's remarks on terrorism and a

01:42.736 --> 01:46.139 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
number of other subjects after the news summary.

01:46.173 --> 01:51.278 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In the day's other news, Wall Street went
down hard. The sell-off was driven by falling

01:51.311 --> 01:56.717 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
oil prices, the Chinese economy and foreign
reaction to the Federal Reserve's interest

01:56.750 --> 02:03.390 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
rate hike. and, losses accelerated late as
a variety of option contracts expired.

02:03.423 --> 02:11.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In the end, the Dow Jones Industrial Average
lost nearly 370 points, to close below 17,130,

02:11.598 --> 02:17.270 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the NASDAQ fell almost 80 points, and the
S&amp;P 500 dropped 36. For the week, the Dow

02:17.304 --> 02:22.943 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lost nearly 1 percent. The NASDAQ and the
S&amp;P lost a fraction of a percent.

02:22.976 --> 02:28.749 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Congress finished work today on sweeping tax
cut and government funding bills, and headed

02:28.782 --> 02:33.954 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
home for the holidays. The Senate gave final
approval to a package that includes more than

02:33.987 --> 02:42.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a trillion dollars in new federal spending
for 2016, plus $680 billion in tax cuts over

02:42.662 --> 02:43.263 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the next decade.

02:43.296 --> 02:45.032 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

02:45.065 --> 02:47.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SEN. MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), MAJORITY LEADER:
We're proving you can actually enact significant

02:47.334 --> 02:52.739 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
long-term reforms, achieve conservative policy
goals, and get them signed into law. So, I'm

02:52.773 --> 02:58.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
proud of what the new Senate has accomplished.
I'd like to thank the many friends across

02:58.745 --> 03:04.518 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the aisle who joined us in passing so many
bipartisan reforms for the American people.

03:04.551 --> 03:09.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SEN. HARRY REID (D-NV), MINORITY LEADER: Months
ago, Democrats called on Republicans to work

03:09.423 --> 03:16.463 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with us to craft a budget agreement. We outlined
three goals. We wanted to get rid of sequestration.

03:16.496 --> 03:21.868 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We were able to do that. We wanted to make
sure there was parity between defense and

03:21.902 --> 03:28.508 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the middle class. We wanted to make sure we
kept these poison pill riders off the legislation.

03:28.542 --> 03:30.710 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
All three goals we had, we accomplished.

03:30.744 --> 03:32.345 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

03:32.379 --> 03:36.283 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The budget deal already passed in
the House in separate votes yesterday and

03:36.316 --> 03:41.321 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
today. And later, President Obama signed the
legislation into law.

03:41.354 --> 03:46.626 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
European Union leaders vowed today to wage
an "uncompromising fight" against terror.

03:46.660 --> 03:51.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Their summit in Brussels was the first time
the 28 leaders have met since the November

03:51.598 --> 03:57.804 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
attacks in Paris, claimed by the Islamic State
group. The group agreed to beef up immigration

03:57.838 --> 04:04.344 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
controls, to crack down on gun-running and
to freeze financial assets of extremist groups.

04:04.377 --> 04:11.051 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
More than 990,000 migrants have entered Europe
this year from Africa or the Middle East,

04:11.084 --> 04:16.623 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and there is still no end in sight. The International
Organization for Migration put out the new

04:16.656 --> 04:22.529 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
estimate today, and said more than half are
from Syria. In Geneva, a spokesman said people

04:22.562 --> 04:27.901 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
keep coming, despite temperatures getting
colder and sea conditions growing more dangerous.

04:27.934 --> 04:29.703 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

04:29.736 --> 04:31.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOEL MILLMAN, SPOKESMAN, INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATION
OF MIGRATION: The flows are so strong, even

04:31.404 --> 04:39.246 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
now, this late in the year, that perhaps by
Tuesday, or even before then, IOM estimates

04:39.279 --> 04:45.819 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the million person mark will pass. This
is almost five times last year's level, which

04:45.852 --> 04:46.520 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is extraordinary.

04:46.553 --> 04:48.188 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(EDN VIDEO CLIP)

04:48.221 --> 04:53.560 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The agency also reports at least
760 migrants have died so far this year, with

04:53.593 --> 04:57.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more than half of those in just the last two
months alone.

04:57.531 --> 05:03.136 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Prospects for peace in Yemen hit a new stumbling
block today. Talks in Switzerland were halted

05:03.170 --> 05:08.642 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
after Shiite Houthi rebels suspended all meetings
with Yemen's government. The Houthis blamed

05:08.675 --> 05:14.781 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
repeated violations of a cease-fire in Yemen.
Both sides have ignored the truce, and troops

05:14.814 --> 05:20.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
loyal to the government captured a provincial
capital today, after two days of fighting.

05:20.554 --> 05:27.160 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In Iraq, the U.S. military says Kurdish forces
backed by heavy coalition air strikes beat

05:27.194 --> 05:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
back two major Islamic State attacks this
week. In the north, 500 fighters tried to

05:33.166 --> 05:39.272 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
breach Kurdish positions, and at least 180
were killed. In the west, others attacked

05:39.306 --> 05:41.841 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
government lines outside Ramadi.

05:41.875 --> 05:44.344 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The briefer spoke on a video link from Baghdad:

05:44.377 --> 05:46.046 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

05:46.079 --> 05:51.518 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COL. STEVEN WARREN, U.S. ARMY: In each place,
ISIL was able to muster an offensive effort,

05:51.551 --> 05:55.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
which tells us that they've still got some
fight left in them. However, and much more

05:56.022 --> 06:01.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
importantly, in each fight Iraqi forces were
able to rebuff ISIL's efforts.

06:01.528 --> 06:03.163 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

06:03.196 --> 06:07.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Meanwhile, Defense Secretary Ash
Carter spent the day in Afghanistan, promising

06:07.100 --> 06:12.505 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
U.S. support in the face of a growing Islamic
State presence there. Carter's one-day visit

06:12.539 --> 06:18.612 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
came after the U.S. commander in Afghanistan
warned that ISIS militants from Syria and

06:18.645 --> 06:25.185 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Iraq are gathering in the east. They're joining
like-minded Afghans to gain a foothold there.

06:25.218 --> 06:30.890 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In the U.S. presidential race, the Bernie
Sanders campaign accused the Democratic National

06:30.924 --> 06:36.429 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Committee today of actively aiding frontrunner
Hillary Clinton. The dispute began with an

06:36.463 --> 06:42.802 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
accidental breach of the DNC's database for
voters. For half an hour, Sanders staffers

06:42.836 --> 06:49.943 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
then allegedly used it to access some of Clinton's
voter data and the DNC has now cut off the

06:49.976 --> 06:52.345 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Sanders access to all of its records.

06:52.379 --> 06:54.047 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

06:54.080 --> 06:57.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFF WEAVER, SANDERS CAMPAIGN MANAGER: The
leadership of the DNC is now actively attempting

06:57.450 --> 07:03.923 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to undermine our campaign. This is unacceptable.
Clearly in this case, it looks like they are

07:03.957 --> 07:05.892 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
trying to help the Clinton campaign.

07:05.925 --> 07:07.727 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

07:07.761 --> 07:13.099 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The Sanders campaign fired its data
director for misusing the Clinton voter information.

07:13.133 --> 07:18.672 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And later, it filed suit to regain access
to the Democratic voter data. For its part,

07:18.705 --> 07:23.209 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the DNC rejected the accusation that it's
playing favorites.

07:23.243 --> 07:28.815 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Chicago policeman who fatally shot a black
teenager last year had his first court appearance

07:28.848 --> 07:34.554 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
today since being indicted. Jason Van Dyke
is charged with first-degree murder and official

07:34.587 --> 07:41.261 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
misconduct. Police video released last month
shows him shooting Laquan McDonald sixteen

07:41.294 --> 07:46.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
times. It triggered protests, it forced the
police chief to quit, and prompted federal

07:46.466 --> 07:48.034 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
investigations.

07:48.068 --> 07:54.274 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And China's capital city is now under its
second smog red alert this month. The wave

07:54.307 --> 08:01.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of airborne pollution is forecast to hit Beijing
from Saturday into Tuesday. Today, signs warned

08:01.081 --> 08:06.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people of the risk and ordered half the city's
cars off the road.

08:06.219 --> 08:11.591 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Officials said particle levels will be more
than 20 times what is considered safe by the

08:11.624 --> 08:14.160 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
World Health Organization.

08:14.194 --> 08:18.998 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Still to come on the NEWSHOUR: The president's
priorities for his last year in office; a

08:19.032 --> 08:24.704 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
resolution for peace in Syria; Mark Shields
and David Brooks on the week's news, and much

08:24.738 --> 08:28.575 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
more.

08:28.608 --> 08:32.479 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

08:32.512 --> 08:41.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Back now to President Obama's final
news conference of 2015. Today's session in

08:41.521 --> 08:46.226 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the White House briefing room was a combination
year-in-review and year-to-come.

08:46.259 --> 08:47.861 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

08:47.894 --> 08:53.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: As I look back on this year, the one
thing I see is that so much of our steady,

08:53.833 --> 08:59.139 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
persistent work over the years is paying off
for the American people in big, tangible ways.

08:59.172 --> 09:04.177 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: It was an upbeat assessment from
a president soon to enter his final year in

09:04.210 --> 09:10.483 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
office. He claimed a list of successes -- among
them, job growth and a surge of sign-ups for

09:10.517 --> 09:13.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
health care coverage -- and he promised more
to come.

09:13.553 --> 09:17.457 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: For all the very real progress America's
made over the past seven years, we still have

09:17.490 --> 09:22.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some unfinished business. And I plan on doing
everything I can with every minute of every

09:22.662 --> 09:28.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
day that I have left as president, to deliver
on behalf of the American people. Since taking

09:28.034 --> 09:32.906 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this office, I have never been more optimistic
about a year ahead than I am right now. And

09:32.939 --> 09:36.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in 2016, I'm going to leave it out all on
the field.

09:36.342 --> 09:42.182 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: At the same time, Mr. Obama acknowledged
the growing challenge of confronting terrorism

09:42.215 --> 09:47.620 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at home and abroad, after the attacks in Paris
and San Bernardino, California.

09:47.654 --> 09:51.891 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Even so, he vowed to defeat the Islamic State
group.

09:51.925 --> 09:58.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: And we're going to do so by systematically
squeezing them, cutting off their supply lines,

09:58.598 --> 10:03.636 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
cutting off their financing, taking out their
leadership, taking out their forces, taking

10:03.670 --> 10:05.405 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
out their infrastructure.

10:05.438 --> 10:13.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now, in order for us to stamp them out thoroughly,
we have to eliminate lawless areas in which

10:13.947 --> 10:20.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they cannot still roam. So, we can disable
them, we can dismantle much of their infrastructure

10:20.753 --> 10:27.894 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and greatly reduce the threat that they pose
to the United States our allies and our neighbors.

10:27.927 --> 10:33.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our long term goal has to be to stabilize
areas so that they don't have any safe haven.

10:33.399 --> 10:37.904 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And in order for us to do that in Syria, there
has to be an end to the civil war.

10:37.937 --> 10:43.476 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Today, in fact, the U.N. Security
Council approved a resolution that outlines

10:43.510 --> 10:49.983 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a process for a limited cease-fire in Syria,
and peace talks. The U.S. wants the ouster

10:50.016 --> 10:55.088 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Syrian President Bashar al-Assad, while
Russia supports him.

10:55.121 --> 10:59.125 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But President Obama made clear Assad is still
a central problem.

10:59.158 --> 11:06.399 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: Assad is going to have to leave in
order for the country to stop the blood letting

11:06.432 --> 11:12.305 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and for all the parties involved to be able
to move forward in a nonsectarian way. And

11:12.338 --> 11:18.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I do think that you've seen from the Russians
a recognition that after a couple of months,

11:18.711 --> 11:23.583 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they're not really moving the needle that
much, despite sizable deployment inside of

11:23.616 --> 11:31.157 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Syria. And, of course, that's what I suggested
would happen, because there is only so much

11:31.190 --> 11:39.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
bombing you can do when an entire country
is outraged and believes that its ruler doesn't

11:39.832 --> 11:41.434 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
represent them.

11:41.467 --> 11:46.673 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The news conference also came just
days after more than 190 nations reached a

11:46.706 --> 11:50.176 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
landmark deal on arresting climate change.

11:50.209 --> 11:53.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president brushed aside Republican opposition
to the deal.

11:53.947 --> 12:00.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: Right now, the American Republican
Party is the only major party that I can think

12:00.553 --> 12:09.829 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of in the advanced world that effectively
denies climate change. I mean, it's an outlier.

12:09.862 --> 12:14.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, my sense is, is this is something that
may be an advantage in terms of short term

12:14.901 --> 12:19.739 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
politics in the Republican primary; it's not
something that is going to be a winner for

12:19.772 --> 12:21.374 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Republicans long term.

12:21.407 --> 12:25.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: On the other hand, the president
praised Republican House Speaker Paul Ryan's

12:25.745 --> 12:29.182 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
work on crafting the 2016 budget compromise.

12:29.215 --> 12:35.888 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: It was a good win. And there are some
things in there that I don't like, but that's

12:35.922 --> 12:41.527 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the nature of legislation and compromise.
And I think the system worked. That gives

12:41.561 --> 12:50.236 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
