This is just one step in other words of trying

17:45.765 --> 17:48.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to maintain the momentum to get to the political
resolution.

17:48.567 --> 17:52.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: And getting to the cease fire,
you have to know who's on which side of the

17:52.204 --> 17:52.605 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
table.

17:52.638 --> 17:54.273 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
WARNER: Right.

17:54.307 --> 17:58.010 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: I mean, who exactly is the enemy
of Assad, which countries think should be

17:58.044 --> 17:59.011 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at the table.

17:59.045 --> 18:01.013 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WARNER: Very important point.

18:01.047 --> 18:06.218 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The opposition which have never agreed on
anything finally had a meeting in Riyadh a

18:06.252 --> 18:10.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
