that then will choose the group to sit at

18:10.423 --> 18:12.858 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the table, OK? It's very indirect.

18:12.892 --> 18:17.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But meanwhile, all these other countries,
all of them, have different candidates that

18:17.863 --> 18:23.736 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they want to nominate for too much of the
terrorist to be at the table. So, they include

18:23.769 --> 18:27.473 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some groups that have been clients of Iran,
some of them clients of Saudi Arabia. All

18:27.506 --> 18:32.511 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of that is still unresolved. Jordan is supposed
to be coordinating this, poor Jordan, so that

18:32.545 --> 18:34.013 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
all remains to be÷}ijf÷ resolved.

18:34.046 --> 18:35.715 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: So, big first step today.

18:35.748 --> 18:40.987 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But thank you very much, Margaret Warner.

18:41.020 --> 18:45.591 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WARNER: My pleasure.

