19:31.871 --> 19:34.440 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS, THE NEW YORK TIMES: Yes, there
are a couple of layers here. The first one

19:34.473 --> 19:37.843 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is, he said quite accurately, we can't stop
all the lone wolves. You had a couple out

19:37.877 --> 19:40.413 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there in San Bernardino. Obviously, we can't
stop that.

19:40.446 --> 19:46.552 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Are we making progress? He claims we are.
That's highly disputed. ISIS remains magnetic.

19:46.585 --> 19:50.923 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're drawing more forces, sometimes they
take ground, sometimes they lose ground, it's

19:50.956 --> 19:53.959 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not clear that we're necessarily making progress
against him.

19:53.993 --> 19:57.997 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The third thing and the biggest backdrop is,
we've just had for six years, an existentially

19:58.030 --> 20:03.569 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
weak policy in that area. You know, he drew
a red line with Assad, he ignored it, he was

20:03.602 --> 20:07.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
asked by people in his own administration
to be more aggressive with ISIS, early on,

20:07.540 --> 20:09.308 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he wasn't.

20:09.341 --> 20:14.547 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In my view, we left Iraq too early and destabilized
the region. So, the existential issue is one

20:14.580 --> 20:19.251 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of passivity. And so, we made some progress
recently, but I would not -- but he's arguing

20:19.285 --> 20:23.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from a place of weakness because of the things
-- the mistakes that were made in the past.

20:23.722 --> 20:25.391 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Existentially weak position?

20:25.424 --> 20:30.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS, SYNDICATED COLUMNIST: Yes, rather
than relitigate that, I mean, 14 years of

20:30.329 --> 20:38.871 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
war, there is no appetite in this country
for military intervention in the Middle East.

20:38.904 --> 20:44.643 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president, I think, most recently has
been caught flat-footed in understandable

20:44.677 --> 20:50.349 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
change in public interest, priorities and
concerns. I mean, you have the Russian airliner,

20:50.382 --> 20:57.223 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
vacation civilians shot down by the same group
that then has the attack on Paris and paralyzes

20:57.256 --> 21:02.595 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the great city at night and then it's followed
up at least by disciples in San Bernardino

21:02.628 --> 21:06.665 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
massacring civilians at a Christmas party.

21:06.699 --> 21:13.105 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's understandable switch, a sea change
in American attitude and concerns, and from

21:13.139 --> 21:21.480 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the economy and jobs, to personal safety and
survival and concern about terrorism. The

21:21.514 --> 21:25.918 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
White House, the president in particular,
just didn't pick that up. I don't know why.

21:25.951 --> 21:27.620 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Why not?

21:27.653 --> 21:32.324 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SHIELDS: I don't know why, somebody suggested,
disdain for cable news that -- or whatever,

21:32.358 --> 21:42.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know. But he didn't. What's been missing,
I would suggest, rather than policy, because

21:42.034 --> 21:46.172 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Norman Schwarzkopf, the great general, said
it doesn't take courage to order men into

21:46.205 --> 21:49.542 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
battle, it does take courage to go into battle.

21:49.575 --> 21:55.481 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The opposition right now is talking loosely
about going in, and getting tough and kicking

21:55.514 --> 22:00.953 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
tail and all the rest of it, but what is missing
is any sense of resoluteness, or strength

22:00.986 --> 22:06.292 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the president. He talks about it like he's
talking about the gross domestic product and

22:06.325 --> 22:09.161 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
how it's grown and interest rates.

22:09.195 --> 22:10.863 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There isn't, to me, anyway --

22:10.896 --> 22:15.701 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BROOKS: I agree. He hasn't reflected the fear
people feel, the concern people feel, that

22:15.734 --> 22:17.670 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
-- even the anger and outrage people feel.

22:17.703 --> 22:19.271 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
SHIELDS: Yes.

22:19.305 --> 22:22.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BROOKS: But that's because of who -- he
who says A must say B. And so, if you don't

22:22.641 --> 22:28.414 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
want to get to -- if he says A, outrage, serious
problem, you have to have a new and aggressive

22:28.447 --> 22:33.485 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
policy, which he doesn't want to have. He
believes in the current policy. It's a moderately

22:33.519 --> 22:37.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
aggressive, maybe. But if he wanted to step
up the rhetoric, he'd have to step up the

22:37.456 --> 22:41.527 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
action and he doesn't want to step up the
reaction, therefore, he can't say really,

22:41.560 --> 22:43.229 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
verbalize much.

22:43.262 --> 22:46.398 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Well, how do you measure resoluteness?
I mean, Mark, you're saying because of his

22:46.432 --> 22:54.240 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
